    <text id="B2033T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Smith informs Manly that Corliss should not plan to teach at Staunton, as the
                    post has already been filled by John Scott, a well-known former teacher
                there.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    American Missionary Association,<lb/>No. 53 John Street,<lb/><abbr
                        expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr> Edw. P. Smith, <abbr expan="General"
                            >Gen'l</abbr> Field Agent
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr> R. M. Manly<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Superintendent">Supt.</abbr> of <abbr expan="Education"
                        >Ed.</abbr> for <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr><lb/>Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-09-10"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 10 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Our attention has been called to your recommendation to Mr. Corliss to occupy
                    Staunton.</p>

                <p>Mr. John Scott who has previously taught there, and is known favorably to the
                    people, has already made arrangements to go there.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Truly Yours</salute>
                    <signed>Edw<hi rend="super">d</hi> P. Smith</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">per <unclear>S.A.T.</unclear></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
